# 🎵 Spotify Clone

A sleek Spotify Clone built using **React**, styled with **Tailwind CSS**, and powered by the **Spotify81 API** from [RapidAPI](https://rapidapi.com/). Search and play your favorite tracks, explore albums and artists — all from an intuitive, fast UI.

---

## 🚀 Technologies Used

* React – Frontend library for building UI
* Tailwind CSS – Utility-first CSS framework for rapid styling
* RapidAPI – Used for fetching music data via Spotify81 API
* Spotify API – Used for playback and detailed media data

---

## ⚙️ Getting Started

Follow these steps to run the project locally:

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/spotify-clone.git
   cd spotify-clone
   ```

2. Install dependencies:

   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. Start the development server:

   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

4. Open in your browser:
   Visit [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173)

---

## 🔑 API Setup

This project uses the Spotify81 API via RapidAPI. To use it:

1. Sign up at [RapidAPI](https://rapidapi.com/)
2. Subscribe to the [Spotify81 API](https://rapidapi.com/project-spotify81/api/spotify81/)
3. Copy your API Key
4. Create a `.env` file in the project root and add:

   ```env
   VITE_RAPIDAPI_KEY=your_api_key_here
   ```

---

## 🎧 Features

* 🔍 Search for tracks, albums, and artists
* 🎵 Play selected tracks
* 💿 View full album details and track listings
* 🎨 Responsive and modern UI
* ⚡ Fast performance with instant results

